Key Match Events: Austria scored their second goal with a powerful header from Romano Schmid (59’), which was deflected in by Stefan De Vrij.
Netherlands equalized through Cody Gakpo (47’), showing incredible composure to slot it in.
Memphis Depay scored for Netherlands (75’), but Austria regained the lead in the 80th minute with a fluid move ending in a goal by Marcel Sabitzer.
Pre-Game Insights: Netherlands manager Ronald Koeman urged his team to go higher up the pitch but struggled initially due to an own goal.
Austria dominated possession in the early going and had a clever counter-press, making it difficult for the Dutch.
Netherlands made a substitution after 35 minutes with Simons replacing Veerman, leading to a more dynamic Dutch play.
Post-Match Reflections: Austria manager praised his team’s intensity and determination in winning the match.
Netherlands manager Ronald Koeman was livid with his team’s performance, especially after conceding an own goal.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria won Group D and will now face the second-placed team from Group F in Leipzig.
The Netherlands qualified for the knockout stages as a best third-placed side and may face England in the next round.
